description: A swath of the eastern U.S. braced for more severe weather after deadly storms knocked out power to hundreds of thousands across the South and disrupted airport travel in the Northeast.
title: After severe weather across the South, East Coast braces for potential flooding, tornadoes

description: The company, which is a minority-owned federal contractor, will pay a penalty and be monitored to ensure compliance with U.S. anti-discrimination laws.
title: After ‘whites only’ job posting, tech staffing firm settles with DOJ, Labor

description: Walton starred for the UCLA Bruins before an influential but injury-derailed NBA career in Portland, San Diego and Boston. Afterward, he became one of the biggest stars in basketball broadcasting.
title: Bill Walton, a Hall of Fame player who became a star broadcaster, dies of cancer at 71

description: A U.S. congressional delegation met the self-governing island's new leader on Monday, and expressed full commitment to supporting Taiwan militarily, diplomatically and economically.
title: U.S. lawmakers vow support for Taiwan and its president after China's military drills

description: Opposing petition drives in Nebraska could present voters with competing choices on abortion. The one with the most votes wins.
title: Nebraska activists seek to put opposing abortion questions on the ballot

description: Anne Banfield left West Virginia in early 2022 and is now an OB-GYN in Maryland. As the 2024 election approaches, she fears more change and uncertainty is on the way.
title: After leaving a so-called 'abortion desert,' this doctor worries about what's next

description: There are lots of reasons people have to stop taking the new weight loss drugs: cost, shortages, side effects and life events. And the weight usually comes back, doctors say.
title: The new obesity drugs work, but it's a dilemma when people have to stop taking them

description: Palestinian health workers said Israeli airstrikes hit tents for displaced people in the southern Gaza city and “numerous” others were trapped in flaming debris.
title: Palestinian medics say Israeli airstrikes kill 35 in Rafah
